              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>(an idiom, literally: to put down the neck) willingly and purposely to expose oneself to extreme danger and risk</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to risk one’s life</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In some instances one can translate this expression in {S:04501600400016} as ‘who showed they were willing to die in order that I could live’ or ‘in order to help me continue to live, they almost died.’</Comments>
